reviews.review: It was better than I thought it would be but not what you would want from such an epic series.
The movie did a real great job of tying everything together. I am not saying  to much except it is a must see for true star wars fans.
It was ok...glad the saga is finally over..lets move on and let the skywalkers rest in peace....best to all in 2020...peace and love...
Fixing a lot from TLJ is a bit too obvious but - TROS is a good SW movie
I loved the integration of all the past and present characters of the Star Wars Characters. And the way the unforeseeable kept me on my toes.
Bad pacing, overpowered main character that had no development, seemed like watching a videogame (fetch quests, lots of explosions). Villain never stood a chance.

This is a fundamentally bad movie with lazy plotting, unengaging characters and actors who really look like they've had enough and just want to take they paycheck and run. However, JJ Abrams trademark frenetic pace means that the 2.5 hours it is on passses relatively quickly and is only really painful to watch during periods in the 2nd half of the movie, hence it receives 2 stars from me, not 1. Many people have said you need to switch your brain off for this movie to enjoy it (and on that basis seem to think that it deserves 5 stars). In my case switching my brain off made it just about bareable for the 1st 45 minutes before it started to get eye rollingly bad to the extent that I wanted to laugh. None of the 5 people i went to see it with (all original trilogy fans) had a good thing to say about it other than that the time passed relatively quickly for such a long movie. In trying to undo the wrongs of The Last Jedi, Disney have made an equally bad movie, but for different reasons.

A waste of money on a movie with no scenario, no proper characters and absolutely no stakes to the whole action. Just mindless fast-paced sequences with terrible editing. I have been a star wars fan for 30 years. This is the first time I was bored during a star wars movie.

What a waste of time and money. And I thought the last two were bad.  How does this movie even fit in with all the other Star Wars movies? I hope this is the last one, they should have stopped at "The Return of the Jedi"
